node.text:
Why are mobile homes so affordable? 

Because they are mass produced and built on assembly lines, manufactured homes cost less to make and therefore less to buy.

Thanks to a lower base price, you can often add upgrades to a manufactured home that you couldn't afford in a traditional stick-built house. 

Manufactured housing makes upgrades like a soaking tub, fireplace or granite countertops much more attainable. 

You can even skip the extras and add square footage to the house, getting a bigger living space for less.

Curious to learn how mobile homes are a great investment? Click the link in the bio & check out the Free Webinar “How we made $10k in 30 days” 
.

node.text:
Let’s talk “Getting Unstuck & Getting to the Bag” 
.
Starting my entrepreneurial journey in 2017 I was very stuck. Stuck in my head, stuck in not believing in myself, stuck in not knowing if I made the right decision for full time entrepreneurship over going back to a job I hated and stuck in not knowing my worth that I am worthy of this lifestyle that I never thought was possible. 
.
. 
You know what got me unstuck, helping families get affordable housing. Helping my people secure financial freedom through a sector that was unheard of and knowing the impact I have on these changed lives. But on top of that, being around like-minded women, women who I can laugh hysterically with, kick it with but also hold me accountable to ensure we are all “Getting to the bag” 🤑
.
.
That is why I am coming together with my sisters @rashaunascott @bryana.randolph @wanakeemarie to bring you B.U.I.L.D & brunch where we will be discussing Branding, Unifying, Impacting, Leading & Diversifying amongst women who are ready to go to that next level.
.
.
Are you ready to join us at the 7 figure table? Come sit down with us for an intimate VIP brunch & intensive panel where you will leave inspired, encouraged and feeling no doubts of wanting to knock down every goal you have this year.

Building relationships are key 🔑 in this business.

Our big bro @beyondwynn & @wall_street_trapper always talk about relationship equity & that relationships go further than money. This is so true in our business.

We genuinely care about the people we do business with. It shows in the many transactions we are able to do. Are you cultivating relationships in your business? Or are you just caring about what’s in it for you, and wondering why you can’t seem to go further in your business?

Focus on building relationships & tap into a new way to do business.

Learn the strategies we share about building relationships in mobile home investing today. Click the link in the bio to get started.
